<H3><A NAME="News4"><FONT  COLOR=#800000>NEWS RELEASE			
NOVEMBER 7, 1996</FONT></A></H3>
<P>
<B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<BR>November 7, 1996</P>
<P>
Lajuanda J. Holder<BR>
Director of Investor Relations<BR>
(915)688-3419<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:cwei@worldnet.att.net">email - cwei@worldnet.att.net</A></P></B>
<CENTER><B>
CLAYTON WILLIAMS ENERGY<BR>ANNOUNCES COTTON VALLEY SEISMIC CONTRACT</B></CENTER>
<P>
Midland, Texas, November 7, 1996 -- Clayton Williams Energy, Inc. (NASDAQ-NMS:CWEI) announced today that it has signed a contract with Tidelands Geophysical Co., Inc. of Plano, Texas pursuant to which Tidelands will conduct a 3-D seismic survey over an approximate 20,000 acre Company-owned leasehold position in Robertson County, Texas.  The seismic survey will evaluate the Company's acreage for the potential presence of Cotton Valley pinnacle reefs.  Cost of the survey, including interpretation, is expected to be approximately $3.1 million and the survey is expected to commence, after the completion of preliminary work, in January 1997.  The Company anticipates that the survey will be completed during the first quarter of 1997 and that the resulting data will be interpreted during the secondquarter of 1997.
<P>
Clayton Williams Energy, Inc. is an independent energy company located in Midland, Texas.
</P>
