<H3><A NAME="News2"><FONT  COLOR=#800000>NEWS RELEASE			
OCTOBER 7, 1996</FONT></A></H3>
<P>
<B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<BR>October 7, 1996</P>
<P>
Lajuanda J. Holder<BR>
Director of Investor Relations<BR>
(915)688-3419<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:cwei@worldnet.att.net">email - cwei@worldnet.att.net</A></P></B>
<CENTER><B>
CLAYTON WILLIAMS ENERGY<BR>ANNOUNCES FILING</B></CENTER>
<P>
Midland, Texas, October 7, 1996 - Clayton Williams Energy, Inc.  (NASDAQ -NMS: CWEI) announced today that it has filed a registration statement with the Securities and Exchange Commission  for an offering of 1,250,000 shares of common stock.  The managing underwriters for the Offering are Rodman & Renshaw, Inc. and Hanifen, Imhoff, Inc.  The Company has granted the underwriters an option to purchase an additional 187,500 shares of common stock solely for the purpose of covering an over-allotment.</P>
<P>
Proceeds from the Offering will be used initially to reduce the Company's bank indebtedness. The Company intends to use its increased borrowing capacity, together with internally generated funds, to finance its 1997 capital expenditure program and an estimated $5 million to conduct, and evaluate, a 3-D seismic survey in search of Cotton Valley pinnacle reef formations on a portion of its updip block in the Giddings field.</P>
<P>
A registration statement relating to these securities has been filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission but has not yet become effective. These securities may not be sold nor may offers to buy be accepted prior to the time the registration statement becomes effective. This communication shall not constitute an offer to sell or the solicitation of an offer to buy, nor shall there be any sale of these securities in any state in which such offer, solicitation or sale would be unlawful prior to registration or qualification under the securities laws of any such state.</P>
<P>
Clayton Williams Energy, Inc. is an independent energy company located in Midland, Texas.</P>
