<P>
<B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<BR>October 1, 1996</P>
<P>
Lajuanda J. Holder<BR>
Director of Investor Relations<BR>
(915)688-3419<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:cwei@worldnet.att.net">email - cwei@worldnet.att.net</A></P></B>
<CENTER><B>CLAYTON WILLIAMS ENERGY<BR>
ANNOUNCES ADDITION OF COTTON VALLEY GEOLOGIST</B></CENTER> 
<P>
Midland, Texas, October 1, 1996 - Clayton Williams Energy, Inc. (NASDAQ - NMS:CWEI) has retained the services of Ed Norwood effective October 1, 1996 to lead its Cotton Valley Reef Exploration Team.  Mr. Norwood was formerly Advanced Senior Geologist with Marathon Oil Company.</P>
<P>
Mr. Norwood was instrumental in the discovery of several major Cotton Valley Reef wells in East Texas for Marathon Oil Company, a leader in the exploration and development of the Cotton Valley Reef Play.  Norwood graduated from West Virginia University in 1957 with a Masters in Geology.  He has 38 years of experience including early geological studies of Alaska's Arctic North Slope prior to the Prudhoe Bay discovery in 1966.</P>
<P>
Clayton W. Williams, Jr., President and CEO said, "Ed will be instrumental in the management, evaluation and exploitation of our Cotton Valley Play."</P>
<P>
Clayton Williams Energy, Inc. is an independent energy company located in  Midland, Texas.</P>
